    [
      "p",
      {
        "class": "intro"
      },
      "During the build process, it might be necessary to access other private repositories containing, for instance, libraries."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      {
        "class": "intro"
      },
      "In case such repositories do not belong to the same user that can clone the main application codebase, it is\npossible to use git credentials codebase."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "how-to-use-git-credentials"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#how-to-use-git-credentials"
        },
        "How to use GIT Credentials"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "The first step is to generate a personal access token: see the ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://help.github.com/articles/creating-a-personal-access-token-for-the-command-line/"
        },
        "github"
      ],
      " or ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucket/app-passwords-828781300.html"
        },
        "bitbucket"
      ],
      " documentation."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Then build an url for the Git Credentials."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "The URL for github looks like:"
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "null"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "https://<username>:<token>@github.com"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "while for bitbucket looks like:"
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "null"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "https://<username>:<token>@bitbucket.org"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "where the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "username"
      ],
      " is the username of the account used to generate the token."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Finally add a secret inside an ",
      [
        "stencil-route-link",
        {
          "url": "/docs/appflow/environments/#custom-environments"
        },
        "environment"
      ],
      " with key called ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "GIT_CREDENTIALS"
      ],
      " and for the value use the url created before."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "img",
        {
          "src": "/docs/assets/img/appflow/cookbook/git-credentials-token-secret.png",
          "alt": "Git credentials token secret"
        }
      ]
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "At this point, if you use this environment during a build, you can access your repository specifying the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "https"
      ],
      " clone url without any token.\nFor instance, if your private repo contains an npm library, the ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "package.json"
      ],
      " would reference it in this way:"
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "json"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token punctuation"
            },
            "{"
          ],
          "\n  ...\n  ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token property"
            },
            "\"dependencies\""
          ],
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token operator"
            },
            ":"
          ],
          " ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token punctuation"
            },
            "{"
          ],
          "\n    ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token property"
            },
            "\"my_super_secret_library\""
          ],
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token operator"
            },
            ":"
          ],
          " ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token string"
            },
            "\"https://bitbucket.org/myorg/my_super_secret_library.git\""
          ],
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token punctuation"
            },
            ","
          ],
          "\n    ...",
          [
            "span",
